was described by 
<collectingMunicipality box="[763,842,167,193]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">French</collectingMunicipality>
from a single male received from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F544023F5B5FFFE619AF06922C23FF33:7832E5F25B5EFFE1183C03E42985FF33" box="[287,434,202,228]" county="Larimer Co." latitude="40.371918" longLatPrecision="1" longitude="-105.52742" municipality="French" name="David Bruce" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" stateProvince="Colorado">David Bruce</location>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[511,622,202,228]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, where he is known to have traveled and collected widely (
<bibRefCitation author="Brown FM" box="[339,489,237,264]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomological Society" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" pagination="126 - 133" part="74" refId="ref17441" refString="Brown FM (1966) David Bruce (1833 - 1903) and Other Entomological Collectors in Colorado. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 74 (3): 126 - 133." title="David Bruce (1833 - 1903) and Other Entomological Collectors in Colorado" type="journal article" year="1966">Brown 1966</bibRefCitation>
