<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="108" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1109,166,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,313,589,615]" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis box="[185,308,589,615]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[326,520,589,615]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[326,520,589,615]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Panthea gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is on average the largest New World species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1820" box="[140,229,624,650]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[140,229,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Panthea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with some females having a wingspan in excess of 
<quantity box="[823,886,624,651]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" unit="cm" value="6.0">6 cm</quantity>
. Only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anweiler" authorityYear="2009" box="[967,1107,624,650]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guatemala">
<emphasis box="[967,1107,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P. guatemala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[316,401,659,685]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[462,586,659,685]" name="Guatemala" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
and some populations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[894,1042,660,685]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virginarius">
<emphasis box="[894,1042,660,685]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P. virginarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the western 
<collectingCountry box="[277,332,695,721]" name="United States of America" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">USA</collectingCountry>
overlap 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[428,545,695,720]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[428,545,695,720]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P. gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size. The male of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[777,899,695,721]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[777,793,695,720]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[808,899,695,720]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the combination of large size (FW length 22-27.5 mm), dark gray-black, or graybrown (
<collectingCountry box="[228,315,765,791]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Mexico</collectingCountry>
only) forewing and contrasting white hindwing, and can be separated from all other New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1820" box="[454,543,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,543,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Panthea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the unique bifurcate uncus. The female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[1084,1100,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[140,231,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Anweiler" authorityYear="2009" box="[600,747,835,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guatemala">
<emphasis box="[600,616,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[634,747,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">guatemala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by range (
<figureCitation box="[876,962,835,862]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="36.[140,174,1654,1676]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,988,1634]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[141,1107,990,1634]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Fig. 70. Distribution of examined specimens of P. gigantea, P. guatemala, and P. reducta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3771598/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
) and by the much less extensively sclerotized ductus bursae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[716,840,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[716,732,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[749,840,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[856,940,871,898]" captionStart="Figures 58-68" captionStartId="35.[140,222,1494,1516]" captionTargetBox="[197,1038,190,1416]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[140,1108,174,1453]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figures 58-68. Panthea female genitalia 58. P. apanthea, Coconino Co, AZ. USA; 59. P. judyae, Chihuahua, MEX; 60. P. gigantea, Chihuahua, MEX; 61. P. guatemala, Oaxaca, MEX; 62. P. virginarius, Missoula Co., MT., USA; 63. P.acronyctoides nigra, Teller Co., CO., USA;. 64. P. a. acronyctoides, Ashland Co., WI, USA; 65. P. f.furcilla, Windham Co., CT, USA; 66. P. f.furcilla-f. nigra intermediate, Dauphin Co., PA., USA; 67. P. furcilla australis, Whitfield Co., GA, USA; 68. Panthea greyi, Apache Co., AZ., USA." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3771594/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) and from the female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[259,414,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virginarius">
<emphasis box="[259,275,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[294,414,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">virginarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[432,518,906,933]" captionStart="Figures 58-68" captionStartId="35.[140,222,1494,1516]" captionTargetBox="[197,1038,190,1416]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[140,1108,174,1453]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figures 58-68. Panthea female genitalia 58. P. apanthea, Coconino Co, AZ. USA; 59. P. judyae, Chihuahua, MEX; 60. P. gigantea, Chihuahua, MEX; 61. P. guatemala, Oaxaca, MEX; 62. P. virginarius, Missoula Co., MT., USA; 63. P.acronyctoides nigra, Teller Co., CO., USA;. 64. P. a. acronyctoides, Ashland Co., WI, USA; 65. P. f.furcilla, Windham Co., CT, USA; 66. P. f.furcilla-f. nigra intermediate, Dauphin Co., PA., USA; 67. P. furcilla australis, Whitfield Co., GA, USA; 68. Panthea greyi, Apache Co., AZ., USA." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3771594/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) by the much larger and more heavily sclerotized sterigma of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="French" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[274,401,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Panthea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis box="[274,290,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="108">P</emphasis>
. 
